thread.title: Sam Houston rallies past Harlandale to improve to 9-0, clinch 28-5A title.
thread.title_full: Sam Houston rallies past Harlandale to improve to 9-0, clinch 28-5A title. - San Antonio Express-News

author: David Hinojosa
title: Sam Houston rallies past Harlandale to improve to 9-0, clinch 28-5A title.
text:
With a perfect regular season in jeopardy, Sam Houston needed a clutch drive.
The Hurricanes got it, and they relied on senior Jawaun Martin to finish it off when he caught a 10-yard TD pass from Raymonte Prime with 1:16 left to lift third-ranked Sam Houston to a 29-23 victory over Harlandale on Friday at Harlandale Memorial Stadium.
The Hurricanes (9-0, 7-0) clinched their second-straight District 28-5A championship. Next week, they can become only the second team in school history to record a 10-0 regular season if they can defeat winless Lanier.
For more, visit ExpressNews.com
